This paper is about neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel graph distillation algorithm, which involves knowledge transfer and optimization, making it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper uses the TED talks multilingual dataset, which involves audio and video processing, making it somewhat relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
